 3+ years of recruiting, administrative, or coordination experience 
 3+ years of experience supporting mid-level to senior management in corporate environments, fast-paced companies, or professional services firms 
 PC skills including working knowledge of Microsoft Office and Outlook tools 
 strong written and verbal communication skills 
 
Are you interested in helping to build out Amazon's R&D teams? Strategic Recruiting cultivates relationships with executive level talent in areas such as artificial intelligence, UX design, speech, robotics, vision, optimization, data and numerical sciences, and economics.
 
The Strategic Recruiting Coordinator (RC) will own the candidate experience, managing the entire candidate life cycle in terms of scheduling, data management, travel arrangements, and on-site experience. Amazon highly values the candidate experience and this associate will be the primary point of contact for candidates in their exploration of Amazon. The RC will also support coordination of recruiting events and programs, such as conferences, faculty summit and open-houses.
 
 **This role can be based in the following locations: 
Chicago, IL
 New York, NY
 Austin, TX
 Nashville, TN
 Seattle, WA
 
 This role will influence candidate and client experience by: 
 
 Ensuring an excellent candidate experience through prompt follow up and communication with executive candidates throughout the candidate’s life cycle from initial contact to start date 
 Ensuring on-site candidates have a positive interviewing experience at Amazon by being their main point of contact throughout their day and ensuring the interview schedule flows smoothly 
 Entering and tracking candidate information in Amazon database and ensuring a high standard of data integrity 
 Experience working with applicant tracking systems 
 Experience working with executive recruiting teams 
 Experience using data to identify process improvement opportunities 
 Ability to handle confidential information and escalate issues when appropriate 
 Comfortable in a fast-paced environment and dealing with ambiguity 
 
